reason.tex:
%text If a random variable $(X)$ can have \underline\text{only} values from the set $\lbrace x_1, x_2, \ldots x_n\rbrace$, then it's \underline\text{probability distribution} is defined as
% \begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|} \hline X & x_1 & x_2 & \ldots & x_N \\ \hline P(X=x_i) & p_1 &p_2& \ldots & p_N \\ \hline \end{tabular}
%text
\textbf{Moreover, \[ \sum_{i=1}^n p_i = 1 \]}
